Sentencas: This paper describes the fabrication of Ni0.6Zn0.4-Gd0.2Ce0.8O2-delta (NiZn-GDC) via a two-step wet chemical synthesis technique.
Titulo: An efficient carbon resistant composite Ni0.6Zn0.4O2-δ-GDC anode for biogas fuelled solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: This composite was found to be more thermally stable and carbon resistive under the intense reducing environment of biogas.
Titulo: An efficient carbon resistant composite Ni0.6Zn0.4O2-δ-GDC anode for biogas fuelled solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: This was confirmed by different characterization techniques.
Titulo: An efficient carbon resistant composite Ni0.6Zn0.4O2-δ-GDC anode for biogas fuelled solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The maximum power density P-max, was achieved at 600 degrees C as 820 mW/cm(2) and 548 mW/cm(2) with hydrogen and biogas, respectively.
Titulo: An efficient carbon resistant composite Ni0.6Zn0.4O2-δ-GDC anode for biogas fuelled solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Different characterization techniques have been performed, such as X-ray diffractometry (XRD), scanning electron microscopy (SEM/EDX), UV visible spectroscopy, and Raman spectroscopy.
Titulo: An efficient carbon resistant composite Ni0.6Zn0.4O2-δ-GDC anode for biogas fuelled solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The XRD pattern by Rietveld refinement showed two-phase structures of the anode composite with an average crystallite size of 25 35 nm before and after reduction with methane.
Titulo: An efficient carbon resistant composite Ni0.6Zn0.4O2-δ-GDC anode for biogas fuelled solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The optical band gap (E-g(opt)) of NiZn-GDC was calculated to be 2.24eV from the Tauc plot using absorbance data.
Titulo: An efficient carbon resistant composite Ni0.6Zn0.4O2-δ-GDC anode for biogas fuelled solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The Nyquist plot was also drawn to study the AC electrochemical impedance spectra (EIS) of the nanocomposite anode from 450 degrees C to 600 degrees C in air.
Titulo: An efficient carbon resistant composite Ni0.6Zn0.4O2-δ-GDC anode for biogas fuelled solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The maximum DC conductivity of 1.37 S/cm was observed at a temperature of 600 degrees C using the four-probe DC technique.
Titulo: An efficient carbon resistant composite Ni0.6Zn0.4O2-δ-GDC anode for biogas fuelled solid oxide fuel cell
